	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories The Ekurhuleni Metro Police Department (EMPD) on Monday nabbed a suspected drug dealer after hours of surveillance by its drug enforcement unit. EMPD spokesperson Chief Superintendent Wilfred Kgasago said officers were surveilling a man in the Springs area after receiving a tip-off "from a reliable source". "The suspect's vehicle was subsequently stopped and searched on Tonk Meter Road near N17 Hospital whereupon various drugs were [discovered] in his vehicle." Kgasago said that police found 25 packets of crystal methamphetamine, cat, heroin and rock – all of which totalled about R12 000. "The 49-year-old [suspect] was detained at Springs police station where he was charged with possession and dealing in illicit substances." He is expected to appear in the Springs Magistrate's Court soon. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  